<headline>Special Weather Statement issued January 12 at 3:08PM EST  by NWS Detroit</headline>
<description>...A WINTER STORM WARNING IS IN EFFECT...
WEATHER...
* Widespread snow is now moving in across the Tri-Cities.
* Air temperatures currently range between 34-35 degrees. This
will initially limit accumulations to grassy or elevated
surfaces through 4 PM. Accumulations on roadways will be
possible after 4 PM as temperatures drop closer to freezing
and snow rates increase.
* East winds around 20 mph with gusts to 30 mph. Highly
fluctuating visibilities to or below 1 mile are expected given
the breezy conditions.
IMPACTS...
* Accumulating snow may lead to slippery roads, particularly on
bridges, exit ramps and overpasses.
* Snow is will bring a reduction in visibility to around 1 mile
or less.
&amp;&amp;
PRECAUTIONARY/PREPAREDNESS ACTIONS...
* Prepare, plan and stay informed. Visit http://go.usa.gov/c7kkP</description>
